            <p>The Hero Xoom 160 is anticipated to launch in India in November 2024, with an estimated price range between ₹1,10,000 and ₹1,20,000. Comparable models currently available include the <a class="for-link" asp-controller="Bajaj" asp-action="BajajPulsar150">Bajaj Pulsar 150</a>, <a class="for-link" asp-controller="Honda" asp-action="HondaUnicorn">Honda Unicorn</a>, and <a class="for-link" asp-controller="Hero" asp-action="HeroXtreme160R">Hero Xtreme 160R</a>.</p>
            <p>Hero MotoCorp recently introduced the Xoom 160 adventure scooter. This scooter marks the Jaipur-based brand’s first foray into off-road-oriented models.</p>
            <p>The Xoom 160 features a robust design and a tall profile. Its front fascia is equipped with a split LED headlight, a clear visor, maxi-scooter styling with a central spine, and a single-piece seat.</p>
            <p>At its core, the Hero Xoom 160 is powered by a 156cc liquid-cooled engine with Hero’s i3s technology, although the exact power output has not yet been disclosed. Additional features include LED lighting, a digital console, a smart key, an ignition dial, remote ignition, and Smart Find functionality.</p>
            <p>In terms of hardware, the Xoom 160 is fitted with telescopic front forks, dual rear shocks, disc brakes on both ends, and 14-inch wheels with block-pattern tires.</p>
            <p>The Hero Xoom 160 is a sportier and more powerful scooter from Hero MotoCorp, designed for urban commuters who seek a mix of performance, style, and advanced features. Here are the key specifications and features of the Hero Xoom 160:</p>
